## 12. Certificate Lifecycle Operations

Atlas CertOps must reliably process:

- New certificate creation.
- Ownership assignment.
- Document attachment.
- Approval routing.
- Rejection and resubmission.
- Renewal.
- Expiration calculation.
- Reminder generation.
- Status transition.
- Archival.
- Audit recording.

Operations personnel should investigate when:

- Expiration jobs do not complete.
- Renewal reminders are duplicated or missing.
- Workflow state becomes inconsistent.
- Certificate attachments cannot be retrieved.
- Customer dashboards disagree with source records.
- Audit events are missing.
- Scheduled reports fail.

Corrections must preserve history rather than silently replacing or deleting evidence.

---

## 13. Background Jobs

Background jobs may include:

- Expiration-status recalculation.
- Renewal-reminder generation.
- Notification dispatch.
- Scheduled report generation.
- Integration synchronization.
- Data-retention processing.
- Search indexing.
- Audit export.
- Backup verification.

For each job, operations documentation must identify:

- Schedule.
- Owner.
- Expected duration.
- Success condition.
- Retry behavior.
- Failure alert.
- Safe manual rerun procedure.
- Duplicate-processing protection.

A failed job must not be rerun until the operator understands whether the previous attempt partially completed.

