## 24. Operational Metrics

Track at minimum:

- Service availability.
- Request latency.
- Error rate.
- Incident count by severity.
- Mean time to acknowledge.
- Mean time to restore.
- Backup success rate.
- Restore-test success rate.
- Notification success rate.
- Background-job failure rate.
- Support response time.
- Capacity utilization.
- Change failure rate.
- Emergency-change frequency.

Metrics should be used to improve operations rather than merely produce reports.

---

## 25. Recordkeeping

Maintain records for:

- Incidents.
- Production changes.
- Access reviews.
- Backup tests.
- Disaster-recovery exercises.
- Customer provisioning.
- Customer offboarding.
- Security exceptions.
- Vendor reviews.
- Maintenance activities.
- Corrective actions.

Records must be protected from unauthorized alteration.

---

## 26. Operational Handoff

Before transferring responsibility to another operator:

- Review active incidents.
- Review pending changes.
- Review failed jobs.
- Review customer escalations.
- Review expiring credentials.
- Review backup status.
- Review unresolved security alerts.
- Document any temporary configuration or workaround.

The receiving operator must have enough information to continue service safely without relying on undocumented verbal knowledge.

